    "Main artifact sources are specifically ocular, cardiac, and (most frequently) muscular artifacts 22.",
    "Many artifact detection/ rejection algorithms have been proposed, relying on both supervised and unsupervised methods.",
    "The work of Khatwani et al.",
    "23 is a relevant example of artifact detection on an in-house dataset, where an energy-efficient convolutional neural network (CNN) processes raw EEG signals without the need for feature extraction and achieves around 74% accuracy.",
